WorldStage Newsonline– International Energy Insurance Plc (IEI), a player in Nigeria’s insurance sector has announced the resignation of its Managing Director/CEO, Mr Peter Irene with effect for December 20, 2020. In a notice at the Nigerian Stock Exchange, the firm said the Chief Operating Officer, Mr Ebunolu Ayeni had taken over in acting capacity pending the approval of the National Insurance Commission for the appointment of a substantial managing director. The notice said Ayeni is a graduate of Insurance from University of Lagos with Master Degree in Marketing and Management from Ladoke Akintola University and Enugu State University respectively. He is a fellow of the Insurance Institute of Nigeria with over three decades of cognitive experience. He is also a member of Nigeria Council of Registered Insurance Brokers and the Institute Of Loans and Risk Management, Nigeria.